affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","K","M","L","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n1584","headword_ar":"اَيْدٌ","root":"Ayd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=dN","text_ar":"ا=دٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n1585","headword_ar":"اَيِّدٌ","root":"Ayd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strong:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K:) an epithet applied [to God, and] to a man. (S.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"ramaY faA^aSaAba AlkulaY waAl*~uraY \n                      \n                     \n                        A_i*aA Alqawosu wat~arahaA A^ay~idN"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When a strong one strings the bow, he shoots, and hits the kidneys, and the tops of the humps of the camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning, when God strings [or stretches] the bow that is in the clouds, He casts fat into the kidneys and humps of the camels, by means of the herbage that is produced by the rain. (S.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laA^ay~idu AlgadaA='i waAlEa$aA='i","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَاَيِّدُ الغَدَا=ءِ وَالعَشَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is often present at the morning and evening meals."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","Msb","K"]}]}}